race.comment: KENTUCKY ROSE (4) resumes here but the form she showed when last in work was good enough to be competitive in this contest. Revved up for this with a recent trial and has placed over this track and trip. Rates the testing material. ADDICTIVE PIRANHA (9) has been thereabouts in recent efforts and is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley. Looms as the main danger. NIRVANA THE STORM (5) is another first-up but has placed when fresh before and has definite top-three claims if he brings his A-game. MHASAHN (10) has put back-to-back wins together either side of the spell and gets 3kg off from the low draw. Plenty to like about his prospects. KWAMI (2) next in line from the Geran barn.
